subsection.def:
Cap. 541D (《第541D章》) means the
                Electoral Affairs Commission (Electoral Procedure) (Legislative Council) Regulation
                    (Cap. 541 sub. leg. D);

Cap. 554 (《第554章》) means the
                Elections (Corrupt and Illegal Conduct) Ordinance (Cap.
                    554);

discontinued election (已中止的選舉) means the general election scheduled to be
                held on the original date pursuant to the Chief Executive’s specification referred
                to in section 3(1);

electoral matter (選舉事宜)—(a)means an act that is done, or purportedly done, under the electoral
                        law; and(b)includes an election related document (as defined by section
                            103(4) of Cap. 541D);

subparagraph.content:
“election period (選舉期間)
                        means the period beginning with 18 July 2020 and ending with 31 July 2020;”;
